  "text": "MDA-MB-231 cells (5610 [CITATION_1] ) were transfected with FLAG-GPR54 constructs (MDA-MB-231 FLAG-GPR54) (25 mg) by electroporation (250 V, 950 mF) using the Gene Pulser Xcell (BioRad, Mississauga, Ontario, Canada) according to the manufacturer's instructions. A heterogeneous population of stable transfectants was selected by using media containing 750 mg/mL G418 (Invitrogen) and expression verified by immunostaining or Western blot for FLAG-GPR54. Gene knockdown of b-arrestin 2 in MDA-MB-231 cells was achieved using shRNA construct (OriGene Technologies, sequence 59-CAGAATCTTCCATGCTCCGTCA-CACTGCA-39, designated shRNA 1) as we have previously described [CITATION_2] . A heterogeneous population of stable transfectants was obtained via puromycin (1 mg/mL) selection. Knockdown of barrestin 2 was verified by Western blot analysis.",
